name: Licensure by endorsement
text: [§465D-9]  Licensure by endorsement.  The director may issue a license by endorsement to an applicant who holds a current and unencumbered license as a behavior analyst in another state; provided that the requirements for a license in that state are deemed by the director to be equivalent to or higher than the current requirements for licensure in this State. [L 2015, c 199, pt of §2]
